      <h1 class='title'>Leave of court required for making of application</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='grand-committee-report-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HL Deb 17 May 2004 vol 661 c313GC</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_313gc' title='Col. 313GC &mdash; HL Deb 17 May 2004 vol 661 c313GC' name='column_313gc' href='#column_313gc' rel='bookmark'>313GC</a>
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-03998'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_609' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        4 (1) No application for an order under paragraph 9 or 13 shall be made unless the leave of the court has been obtained in accordance with rules of court.
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-03999'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_610' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        (2) The court shall not grant leave under this paragraph unless it considers that there is substantial ground for the making of an application for such an order.
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-04000'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_611' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        (3) The court may grant leave under this paragraph notwithstanding that an order has been made by a court in a country outside Northern Ireland requiring the other civil partner to make any payment, or transfer any property, to the applicant or to a child of the family.
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-04001'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_612' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        (4) Leave under this paragraph may be granted subject to such conditions as the court thinks fit.
      </p>
      <ol class='xoxo'>
        
